The paper deals with information flow security properties and their proof from abstract architectural descriptions. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the development of architectural specifications and proofs, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The notion of refinement of system architectures is also mentioned, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
